In a mixing bowl, beat peanut butter, confectioners' sugar, cream cheese and cream until smooth. Add a third of the whipped topping; blend thoroughly. Fold in the remaining whipped topping. Divide and spoon into pastry shells, mounding slightly at edges. Chill. For topping, heat chocolate chips, butter, sugar and cream in a small saucepan until chips are melted. Remove from the heat; add vanilla. Cover and let stand until cool. Spread over top of pies to thin 1 in. of crust. If desired, sprinkle with peanuts. Chill 4 hours before serving. Refrigerate any leftovers.